verbose_text: Irrespective of the protein sample and separation method (1DE or 2DE), spectral cross contamination of other colour channels (blue, green or red) by non specific fluorophore emission signals was low (0.5-2.3% in 1DE gels; Supporting Information Table S1), with the highest cross contamination observed for the Cy3 specific signal in the Cy2 channel (Supporting Information Table S1, Fig. S2).
evidence: Cy3-specific signal in the Cy2 channel
